>[Question]
>what is the min no of circles each of unit area, that can be 
>accomodated completely without any overlap within a circle of 
>radius3/root pi  units?
>
>[Difficulty]
>how to determine the no of circles that can fit in a larger circle
>
>[Thoughts]
>total area of larger circle=9, smaller circle=pi
>hence the area should b 9/pi.. but that is not the correct answer
